SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: A way of contracting a disease through everyday interactions (nonsexual) with an infected person.
A way of contracting a disease by interacting with an individual that has been exposed to the disease while undergoing a medical procedure.
SKOS_CONCEPT.notation: CONTACT WITH EXPOSURE DURING MEDICAL PROCEDURE
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Contact With Exposure During Medical Procedure

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: A way of contracting a disease by physically associating with an infected group of individuals.
SKOS_CONCEPT.notation: CONTACT WITH EXPOSURE IN CROWD SETTING
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Contact With Exposure In Crowd Setting

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: A way of contracting a disease by interacting with an individual that is considered at high risk for having the disease.
A way of contracting a disease through interactions with an infected person in the same residence.
